&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THEATRES, ANAESTHETICS, CRITICAL CARE AND PAIN DIRECTORATE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ASSISTANT DIRECTORATE MANAGER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;30 HOURS PER WEEK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an Assistant Directorate Manager at the Dudley Group NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Directorate Manager for Theatres, Anaesthetics, Critical Care &amp; Pain, you will be responsible for providing day to day operational management within the Directorate, supporting the Directorate Manager, Matron, Clinical Director and Clinical Service Leads to deliver corporate policy, business planning and service development in line with the Trust’s vision, values and strategic goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have proven managerial experience in an operational role, preferably in an NHS setting with experience of involvement in service development and managing change. We are looking for a motivated and flexible individual able to deal effectively with all levels of medical, managerial and administrative staff. You will have excellent communication skills being able to originate and negotiate solutions effectively and sensitively with all grades and professions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based at Russells Hall Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kelly Pettifer, Directorate Manager for Theatres, Anaesthetics, Critical Care &amp; Pain on&lt;strong&gt; 01384 456111 ex 1849&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
